<HEAD>Heartbroken Soldier Runs Amok, Kills Seven, Military Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A soldier went berserk after a quarrel with his girlfriend, firing a rifle at neighbors and villagers and killing seven people, the military said today. The killer surrendered after the rampage, in which nine people were injured, the military said. The report said <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> Negro </PERSON>, a constable at the <ORGANIZATION> Special </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION>, went on the killing spree after he left his girlfriend's home Wednesday in <LOCATION> Tiber </LOCATION>, a village in <LOCATION> Cebu </LOCATION> province 360 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>. The military said the violence was triggered by a `` love problem'' between Negro and the woman, who was not identified. After <PERSON> Negro </PERSON> left his girlfriend's home, he began firing his semiautomatic rifle at neighbors in the coastal village. Five people were killed and five others injured, the report said. <PERSON> Negro </PERSON> then hitched a ride in a jeep to nearby <LOCATION> Talisay </LOCATION> town. While en route, he opened fire on a group of men in <LOCATION> Lawaan </LOCATION> village, killing two and wounding four, the report added. He surrendered later and was undergoing interrogation, the report said.
