</TEXT>
<DATELINE>VANCOUVER, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A small helium balloon launched by elementary school students carried a birthday greeting 1,500 miles in two days, landing eventually in <LOCATION> Saskatchewan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, officials said. `` The students were shocked that it would go that far,'' said <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Little </PERSON>, principal of the <ORGANIZATION> Martin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Luther </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elementary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>. `` They thought that it would go as far as Eastern <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. But to have it go to <LOCATION> Saskatchewan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, was quite a thrill for them.'' Each of the school's 450 students released a helium balloon Nov. 10 bearing the school's blue and yellow colors to mark Veterans Day and the start of the state centennial, <PERSON> Little </PERSON> said. Inside the balloons was the message: `` Happy 100th birthday <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> State from the students and staff of <ORGANIZATION> Martin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Luther </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elementary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>.'' One of the balloons reached the farm of <PERSON> Donna </PERSON> <PERSON> Forrester </PERSON>, who sent the school a letter that said her daughter found the balloon while riding a horse on Nov. 12. `` She was very pleased, to say the least, and we were all amazed that it had come this far,'' <PERSON> Forrester </PERSON> wrote. `` We estimated it traveled about 1,500 miles.'' <PERSON> Forrester </PERSON> enclosed a map of <LOCATION> Saskatchewan </LOCATION> indicating that her farm is about 8 miles north of the U.S.-Canada border along <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dakota </LOCATION>. The students now are getting a lesson in geography and international relations _ two teachers used the map for a lesso