<HEAD>District Attorney Says More Bodies May Be Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DARTMOUTH, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The deaths of four women whose bodies were discovered near highways are related and more bodies may be found as a search of the area continues today, a district attorney said. The bodies were discovered during the last five months, with the latest found Tuesday. `` I feel pretty confident they are connected somehow. There may be more than just the four women,'' <ORGANIZATION> Bristol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Attorney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ronald </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> A. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pina </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday. He said the body found Tuesday `` may be No. 5, not No. 4. There may be another person out there is my concern, if not more.'' Three of the bodies were discovered along Interstate 195 in this southeastern <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> town. The fourth was found along a state road in nearby <LOCATION> Freetown </LOCATION>. Two of the bodies were discovered in July, the other two in November. All four women were believed to have been nude when killed, investigators said. <PERSON> Pina </PERSON> said it was possible that the four deaths were connected with the deaths of two women from <LOCATION> Providence </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> R.I. </LOCATION>, whose bodies were found last spring off highways in southeastern <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>. None of the four more recently found bodies has been identified. <PERSON> Pina </PERSON> said one person may have killed the three women whose bodies were found here, and that the person was familiar with the area. `` The fact that they're all in the same area would lead you to believe that a person has done more than one killing,'' he said. `` There's no doubt that those people were all murdered and left there.'' State Trooper <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Delaney </PERSON> said the bodies were left in similar locations within 15 feet of the tree lines off the highways. But, he said, there also were dissimilarities in the cases. Four women have been listed as missing from nearby <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bedford </LOCATION> in the last several months, but no definite link between them and the bodies has been made.
