<HEAD>`Tenth Man' Tedious; `Maybe Baby' Sophisticated Comedy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Spelling of Rebeca in final graf is cq.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The most irritating thing about Sunday's Hallmark Hall of Fame presentation on <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>, `` The Tenth Man,'' is how self-consciously Important it is. Based on <PERSON> Graham </PERSON> <PERSON> Greene </PERSON>'s intriguing story of a French lawyer imprisoned by the <ORGANIZATION> Nazis </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Hopkins </PERSON> -RRB- who trades his wealth for his life, `` The Tenth Man'' is tedious and overwrought, as exemplified by the cloyingly romantic music overwhelming almost every scene. It's composed by <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Holdridge </PERSON>, who wrote the theme for `` Beauty and the Beast.'' <PERSON> Hopkins </PERSON> can be effecting in the right role, but here he is merely irritating, employing varying degrees of one emotion: dumbfounded. There is some hope when the flamboyant <PERSON> Derek </PERSON> <PERSON> Jacobi </PERSON> bursts on the scene late in the drama to add the final plot twist, but by then it's snoozing time. The movie was shot on location in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>. Why? Most of the scenes are interiors. <PERSON> Hopkins </PERSON> plays <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON>, a successful attorney with an estate outside <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> who is accidentally picked up in a Nazi sweep of innocent citizenry. In prison, he is selected as one of a random few _ every 10th prisoner _ to be executed in retribution against the Resistance. <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON> tries to buy his life, offering everything he has to any man who will take his place in front of the firing squad. <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Mangeot </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Watkins </PERSON> -RRB-, a young man with a bad cough, takes him up on the deal, so he can leave <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON>'s wealth to his mother and sister. Three years later, <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> is liberated, and <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON> returns to his mansion, now in disrepair, where <PERSON> Michel </PERSON>'s mother and sister are living. He conceals his identity and <PERSON> Michel </PERSON>'s attractive sister, <PERSON> Therese </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Kristin </PERSON> <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> -RRB-, hires him as a handyman. She spends most of her spare time imagining how she will kill the hated <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON>. The plot begins to thicken when <PERSON> Jacobi </PERSON> arrives, claiming to be <PERSON> Chavel </PERSON>, but he's mostly lost in the headlong rush to the inexplicable conclusion.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Hal </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Dabney </PERSON> <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> -RRB- and <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Curtin </PERSON> -RRB- have a fabulous life. They live in a beach house, eat exotic foods, drive his-and-hers sports cars and vacation in romantic, out-of-the-way places. <PERSON> Hal </PERSON> is 57 and has two grown children from a previous marriage. He is perfectly satisfied to dote part-time on his two grandchildren. <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> is 39, a career woman who displays little more than mild anxiety when little ones are around _ until her best friend has a baby. `` Maybe Baby,'' previously titled `` Sooner or Later,'' is a cute, sophisticated story of a spoiled woman who thinks having a baby will be as easy as having an <PERSON> Alfa </PERSON> <PERSON> Romeo </PERSON>. It airs Monday on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>. Once <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> convinces herself she needs a baby, she has to convince <PERSON> Hal </PERSON>, who does n't want `` one of those noisy, messy little things'' or to be the only 70-year-old on the sidelines at the Little League games. But he goes along after his secretary -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Florence </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stanley </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- convinces him a 39-year-old woman who's spent 20 years on birth control pills is unlikely to get pregnant. How does she know about the pills? `` Put any two women in the same room and they'll talk about birth control,'' she says. `` It's like men and sports, only infinitely more interesting. Except for a silly scene when <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> finds <PERSON> Hal </PERSON> dining with another woman, `` Maybe Baby'' is funny and plausible. <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Curtin </PERSON> make a nice team, and the supporting roles are nicely played. <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> <PERSON> Duffy </PERSON> -LRB- `` Newhart'' -RRB- plays <PERSON> Hal </PERSON>'s daughter. <PERSON> Janet </PERSON> <PERSON> Kovalcik </PERSON>, who wrote the screenplay, has the confidence to put this line in <LOCATION> Florence </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Stanley </LOCATION>'s mouth: `` This is why I do n't watch soap operas Because the plots are stupid and boring and the people act like jerks.'' But of course that's exactly why we watch soap operas, and movies like `` Maybe Baby.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 Elsewhere in television: CRISIS IN THREE EPISODES _ <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> suffers a heart attack and undergoes surgery in a three-part episode of what usually is <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s comedy `` Family Ties'' that begins this Sunday Anesthesia will allow <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Gross </PERSON> -RRB- to engage in a flashback to his college days with wife, <PERSON> Elyse </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Meredith </PERSON> <PERSON> Baxter </PERSON> <PERSON> Birney </PERSON> -RRB-. <PERSON> Christina </PERSON> <PERSON> Pickles </PERSON>, formerly of `` St. Elsewhere,'' guest stars. ... THEIR DINNER WITH <PERSON> KATE </PERSON> AND <PERSON> ALLIE </PERSON> _ <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Saint </PERSON> <PERSON> James </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Curtin </PERSON> -LRB- `` Kate & amp; <PERSON> Allie </PERSON> -RRB- will guest-star as unsuspecting restaurant patrons caught in a battle of the chefs at `` Tattinger's,'' Dec. 14 on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>. ... EMILY, MEET <PERSON> MOLLY </PERSON>. REALITY, MEET FICTION _ Lifetime <ORGANIZATION> Cablevision </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION>, which picked up `` The Days and Nights of <PERSON> Molly </PERSON> <PERSON> Dodd </PERSON>'' after <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> canceled the series, has signed <PERSON> Shelley </PERSON> <PERSON> Duvall </PERSON>'s production company to create a new show, `` Emily Undercover,'' as a companion for `` Molly'' next April. <PERSON> Emily </PERSON>, uncast, is a former actress who goes to work for a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> private investigation agency. The premise sounds a lot like the real life of <PERSON> Rebeca </PERSON> <PERSON> Arthur </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Perfect Strangers,'' who took a job as a private investigator in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> while struggling to make it as an actress
</TEXT>
