<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 259,285 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's 140,655, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, in which 238,347 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 163,622 cars this week, compared with 89,654 a week ago and 153,907 in the same week in 1987. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 95,663, compared with last week's 51,001 and last year's 84,440. Canadian automakers were to build 17,853 cars this week, up from 17,710 a week ago but down from last year's 20,234. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,024, compared with 21,309 a week ago and 18,491 in the same week last year.
