<HEAD>Mexico Offers Export Reduction to Firm Up OPEC Accord</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAMES ANDERSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> team plans to visit <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and other non-OPEC producing nations to discuss mutual reductions in export quotas, according to a published report Thursday. The report followed an offer by <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> to negotiate a reduction in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s oil exports in a bid to put some teeth into the <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> cartel agreement to restrict production. Energy Secretary <PERSON> Fernando </PERSON> <PERSON> Hiriart </PERSON> this week repeated an offer, previously spurned by the 13-member cartel, to reduce <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s 1.35 million-barrel daily export platform, provided <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> members enact similar reductions. Reductions also would be sought from other independent producers, <PERSON> Hiriart </PERSON> said. He said department officials planned informal talks with <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> and independent producers on possible quota reductions. The <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> announced that an <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> committee plans to visit <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and other independent producers to negotiate reductions to buttress Monday's <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> pact, the <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> newspaper <ORGANIZATION> La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jornada </ORGANIZATION> reported Thursday. Department officials could not be reached for comment Thursday, a national holiday called to mark the inauguration of President <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Salinas </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Gortari </PERSON>. The agreement by the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZAT